{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So today I'm going to talk to you"},{"time":2000,"text":"about the rise of collaborative consumption."},{"time":5000,"text":"I'm going to explain what it is"},{"time":7000,"text":"and try and convince you -- in just 15 minutes --"},{"time":10000,"text":"that this isn't a flimsy idea,"},{"time":12000,"text":"or a short-term trend,"},{"time":14000,"text":"but a powerful cultural and economic force"},{"time":17000,"text":"reinventing not just what we consume,"},{"time":19000,"text":"but how we consume."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"Now I'm going to start with a deceptively simple example."},{"time":24000,"text":"Hands up -- how many of you"},{"time":27000,"text":"have books, CDs, DVDs, or videos"},{"time":30000,"text":"lying around your house"},{"time":32000,"text":"that you probably won't use again,"},{"time":34000,"text":"but you can't quite bring yourself to throw away?"},{"time":37000,"text":"Can't see all the hands,"},{"time":39000,"text":"but it looks like all of you, right?"},{"time":41000,"text":"On our shelves at home,"},{"time":43000,"text":"we have a box set of the DVD series \"24,\""},{"time":46000,"text":"season six to be precise."},{"time":48000,"text":"I think it was bought for us around three years ago for a Christmas present."},{"time":51000,"text":"Now my husband, Chris, and I"},{"time":53000,"text":"love this show."},{"time":55000,"text":"But let's face it, when you've watched it once maybe, or twice,"},{"time":58000,"text":"you don't really want to watch it again,"},{"time":60000,"text":"because you know how Jack Bauer is going to defeat the terrorists."},{"time":63000,"text":"So there it sits on our shelves"},{"time":65000,"text":"obsolete to us,"},{"time":67000,"text":"but with immediate latent value to someone else."},{"time":70000,"text":"Now before we go on, I have a confession to make."},{"time":73000,"text":"I lived in New York for 10 years,"},{"time":75000,"text":"and I am a big fan of \"Sex and the City.\""},{"time":78000,"text":"Now I'd love to watch the first movie again"},{"time":80000,"text":"as sort of a warm-up to the sequel coming out next week."},{"time":83000,"text":"So how easily could I swap"},{"time":85000,"text":"our unwanted copy of \"24\""},{"time":87000,"text":"for a wanted copy of \"Sex and the City?\""},{"time":90000,"text":"Now you may have noticed"},{"time":92000,"text":"there's a new sector emerging called swap-trading."},{"time":94000,"text":"Now the easiest analogy for swap-trading"},{"time":97000,"text":"is like an online dating service"},{"time":99000,"text":"for all your unwanted media."},{"time":101000,"text":"What it does is use the Internet"},{"time":103000,"text":"to create an infinite marketplace"},{"time":105000,"text":"to match person A's \"haves\""},{"time":107000,"text":"with person C's \"wants,\""},{"time":109000,"text":"whatever they may be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"The other week, I went on one of these sites,"},{"time":114000,"text":"appropriately called Swaptree,"},{"time":117000,"text":"and there were over 59,300 items"},{"time":120000,"text":"that I could instantly swap"},{"time":122000,"text":"for my copy of \"24.\""},{"time":125000,"text":"Lo and behold,"},{"time":127000,"text":"there in Reseda, CA was Rondoron"},{"time":129000,"text":"who wanted swap his or her"},{"time":131000,"text":"\"like new\" copy of \"Sex and the City\""},{"time":133000,"text":"for my copy of \"24.\""},{"time":136000,"text":"So in other words, what's happening here"},{"time":138000,"text":"is that Swaptree"},{"time":140000,"text":"solves my carrying company's sugar rush problem,"},{"time":142000,"text":"a problem the economists call \"the coincidence of wants,\""},{"time":145000,"text":"in approximately 60 seconds."},{"time":148000,"text":"What's even more amazing is it will print out a postage label on the spot,"},{"time":151000,"text":"because it knows the way of the item."},{"time":153000,"text":"Now there are layers of technical wonder"},{"time":155000,"text":"behind sites such as Swaptree,"},{"time":158000,"text":"but that's not my interest,"},{"time":160000,"text":"and nor is swap trading, per se."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"My passion, and what I've spent the last few years"},{"time":165000,"text":"dedicated to researching,"},{"time":167000,"text":"is the collaborative behaviors and trust-mechanics"},{"time":170000,"text":"inherent in these systems."},{"time":173000,"text":"When you think about it,"},{"time":175000,"text":"it would have seemed like a crazy idea, even a few years ago,"},{"time":178000,"text":"that I would swap my stuff with a total stranger"},{"time":181000,"text":"whose real name I didn't know"},{"time":183000,"text":"and without any money changing hands."},{"time":186000,"text":"Yet 99 percent of trades on Swaptree"},{"time":188000,"text":"happen successfully,"},{"time":190000,"text":"and the one percent that receive a negative rating,"},{"time":192000,"text":"it's for relatively minor reasons,"},{"time":194000,"text":"like the item didn't arrive on time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"So what's happening here?"},{"time":200000,"text":"An extremely powerful dynamic"},{"time":202000,"text":"that has huge commercial and cultural implications"},{"time":205000,"text":"is at play."},{"time":207000,"text":"Namely, that technology"},{"time":209000,"text":"is enabling"},{"time":211000,"text":"trust between strangers."},{"time":213000,"text":"We now live in a global village"},{"time":215000,"text":"where we can mimic the ties"},{"time":217000,"text":"that used to happen face to face,"},{"time":220000,"text":"but on a scale and in ways"},{"time":222000,"text":"that have never been possible before."},{"time":224000,"text":"So what's actually happening"},{"time":226000,"text":"is that social networks and real-time technologies"},{"time":228000,"text":"are taking us back."},{"time":230000,"text":"We're bartering, trading,"},{"time":232000,"text":"swapping, sharing,"},{"time":234000,"text":"but they're being reinvented"},{"time":236000,"text":"into dynamic and appealing forms."},{"time":238000,"text":"What I find fascinating"},{"time":240000,"text":"is that we've actually wired our world to share,"},{"time":243000,"text":"whether that's our neighborhood, our school,"},{"time":245000,"text":"our office, or our Facebook network,"},{"time":248000,"text":"and that's creating an economy"},{"time":250000,"text":"of \"what's mine is yours.\""},{"time":252000,"text":"From the mighty eBay,"},{"time":254000,"text":"the grandfather of exchange marketplaces,"},{"time":256000,"text":"to car-sharing companies such as GoGet,"},{"time":259000,"text":"where you pay a monthly fee to rent cars by the hour,"},{"time":262000,"text":"to social lending platforms such as Zopa,"},{"time":265000,"text":"that will take anyone in this audience"},{"time":267000,"text":"with 100 dollars to lend,"},{"time":269000,"text":"and match them with a borrower anywhere in the world,"},{"time":272000,"text":"we're sharing and collaborating again"},{"time":275000,"text":"in ways that I believe"},{"time":277000,"text":"are more hip than hippie."},{"time":280000,"text":"I call this \"groundswell collaborative consumption.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"Now before I dig into the different systems"},{"time":285000,"text":"of collaborative consumption,"},{"time":287000,"text":"I'd like to try and answer the question"},{"time":289000,"text":"that every author rightfully gets asked,"},{"time":292000,"text":"which is, where did this idea come from?"},{"time":295000,"text":"Now I'd like to say I woke up one morning"},{"time":297000,"text":"and said, \"I'm going to write about collaborative consumption,\""},{"time":300000,"text":"but actually it was a complicated web"},{"time":302000,"text":"of seemingly disconnected ideas."},{"time":305000,"text":"Over the next minute,"},{"time":307000,"text":"you're going to see a bit like a conceptual fireworks display"},{"time":309000,"text":"of all the dots that went on in my head."},{"time":313000,"text":"The first thing I began to notice:"},{"time":315000,"text":"how many big concepts were emerging --"},{"time":317000,"text":"from the wisdom of crowds to smart mobs --"},{"time":320000,"text":"around how ridiculously easy it is"},{"time":322000,"text":"to form groups for a purpose."},{"time":324000,"text":"And linked to this crowd mania"},{"time":326000,"text":"were examples all around the world --"},{"time":328000,"text":"from the election of a president"},{"time":330000,"text":"to the infamous Wikipedia, and everything in between --"},{"time":332000,"text":"on what the power of numbers could achieve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335000,"text":"Now, you know when you learn a new word,"},{"time":338000,"text":"and then you start to see that word everywhere?"},{"time":341000,"text":"That's what happened to me"},{"time":343000,"text":"when I noticed that we are moving"},{"time":345000,"text":"from passive consumers"},{"time":347000,"text":"to creators,"},{"time":349000,"text":"to highly enabled collaborators."},{"time":352000,"text":"What's happening"},{"time":354000,"text":"is the Internet is removing the middleman,"},{"time":356000,"text":"so that anyone from a T-shirt designer"},{"time":358000,"text":"to a knitter"},{"time":360000,"text":"can make a living selling peer-to-peer."},{"time":362000,"text":"And the ubiquitous force"},{"time":364000,"text":"of this peer-to-peer revolution"},{"time":366000,"text":"means that sharing is happening at phenomenal rates."},{"time":369000,"text":"I mean, it's amazing to think"},{"time":371000,"text":"that, in every single minute of this speech,"},{"time":374000,"text":"25 hours"},{"time":376000,"text":"of YouTube video will be loaded."},{"time":379000,"text":"Now what I find fascinating about these examples"},{"time":382000,"text":"is how they're actually tapping into"},{"time":384000,"text":"our primate instincts."},{"time":386000,"text":"I mean, we're monkeys,"},{"time":388000,"text":"and we're born and bred to share and cooperate."},{"time":390000,"text":"And we were doing so for thousands of years,"},{"time":393000,"text":"whether it's when we hunted in packs,"},{"time":395000,"text":"or farmed in cooperatives,"},{"time":398000,"text":"before this big system called hyper-consumption came along"},{"time":401000,"text":"and we built these fences"},{"time":403000,"text":"and created out own little fiefdoms."},{"time":405000,"text":"But things are changing,"},{"time":407000,"text":"and one of the reasons why"},{"time":409000,"text":"is the digital natives, or Gen-Y."},{"time":412000,"text":"They're growing up sharing --"},{"time":414000,"text":"files, video games, knowledge."},{"time":416000,"text":"It's second nature to them."},{"time":418000,"text":"So we, the millennials -- I am just a millennial --"},{"time":421000,"text":"are like foot soldiers,"},{"time":424000,"text":"moving us from a culture of \"me\" to a culture of \"we.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"The reason why it's happening so fast"},{"time":428000,"text":"is because of mobile collaboration."},{"time":430000,"text":"We now live in a connected age"},{"time":433000,"text":"where we can locate anyone, anytime, in real-time,"},{"time":436000,"text":"from a small device in our hands."},{"time":439000,"text":"All of this was going through my head"},{"time":441000,"text":"towards the end of 2008,"},{"time":443000,"text":"when, of course, the great financial crash happened."},{"time":446000,"text":"Thomas Friedman is one of my favorite New York Times columnists,"},{"time":449000,"text":"and he poignantly commented"},{"time":451000,"text":"that 2008 is when we hit a wall,"},{"time":454000,"text":"when Mother Nature and the market"},{"time":457000,"text":"both said, \"No more.\""},{"time":459000,"text":"Now we rationally know"},{"time":461000,"text":"that an economy built on hyper-consumption"},{"time":464000,"text":"is a Ponzi scheme. It's a house of cards."},{"time":467000,"text":"Yet, it's hard for us to individually know what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470000,"text":"So all of this is a lot of twittering, right?"},{"time":473000,"text":"Well it was a lot of noise and complexity in my head,"},{"time":475000,"text":"until actually I realized it was happening"},{"time":477000,"text":"because of four key drivers."},{"time":479000,"text":"One, a renewed belief in the importance of community,"},{"time":482000,"text":"and a very redefinition of what friend and neighbor really means."},{"time":485000,"text":"A torrent of peer-to-peer social networks"},{"time":488000,"text":"and real-time technologies,"},{"time":490000,"text":"fundamentally changing the way we behave."},{"time":493000,"text":"Three, pressing unresolved environmental concerns."},{"time":496000,"text":"And four, a global recession"},{"time":498000,"text":"that has fundamentally shocked"},{"time":500000,"text":"consumer behaviors."},{"time":502000,"text":"These four drivers"},{"time":504000,"text":"are fusing together"},{"time":506000,"text":"and creating the big shift --"},{"time":508000,"text":"away from the 20th century,"},{"time":510000,"text":"defined by hyper-consumption,"},{"time":512000,"text":"towards the 21st century,"},{"time":514000,"text":"defined by collaborative consumption."},{"time":517000,"text":"I generally believe we're at an inflection point"},{"time":520000,"text":"where the sharing behaviors --"},{"time":522000,"text":"through sites such as Flickr and Twitter"},{"time":524000,"text":"that are becoming second nature online --"},{"time":526000,"text":"are being applied to offline areas of our everyday lives."},{"time":529000,"text":"From morning commutes to the way fashion is designed"},{"time":532000,"text":"to the way we grow food,"},{"time":534000,"text":"we are consuming and collaborating once again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"So my co-author, Roo Rogers, and I"},{"time":542000,"text":"have actually gathered thousands of examples"},{"time":544000,"text":"from all around the world of collaborative consumption."},{"time":546000,"text":"And although they vary enormously"},{"time":548000,"text":"in scale, maturity and purpose,"},{"time":550000,"text":"when we dived into them,"},{"time":552000,"text":"we realized that they could actually be organized into three clear systems."},{"time":555000,"text":"The first is redistribution markets."},{"time":558000,"text":"Redistribution markets, just like Swaptree,"},{"time":561000,"text":"are when you take a used, or pre-owned, item"},{"time":563000,"text":"and move it from where it's not needed"},{"time":565000,"text":"to somewhere, or someone, where it is."},{"time":568000,"text":"They're increasingly thought of as the fifth 'R' --"},{"time":570000,"text":"reduce, reuse, recycle, repair"},{"time":572000,"text":"and redistribute --"},{"time":574000,"text":"because they stretch the life cycle of a product"},{"time":576000,"text":"and thereby reduce waste."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"The second is collaborative lifestyles."},{"time":581000,"text":"This is the sharing of resources"},{"time":583000,"text":"of things like money, skills and time."},{"time":586000,"text":"I bet, in a couple of years,"},{"time":588000,"text":"that phrases like \"coworking\""},{"time":590000,"text":"and \"couchsurfing\" and \"time banks\""},{"time":593000,"text":"are going to become a part of everyday vernacular."},{"time":596000,"text":"One of my favorite examples of collaborative lifestyles"},{"time":599000,"text":"is called Landshare."},{"time":601000,"text":"It's a scheme in the U.K."},{"time":603000,"text":"that matches Mr. Jones,"},{"time":605000,"text":"with some spare space in his back garden,"},{"time":608000,"text":"with Mrs. Smith, a would-be grower."},{"time":611000,"text":"Together they grow their own food."},{"time":613000,"text":"It's one of those ideas that's so simple, yet brilliant,"},{"time":616000,"text":"you wonder why it's never been done before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619000,"text":"Now, the third system"},{"time":621000,"text":"is product-service systems."},{"time":623000,"text":"This is where you pay for the benefit of the product --"},{"time":625000,"text":"what it does for you --"},{"time":627000,"text":"without needing to own the product outright."},{"time":629000,"text":"This idea is particularly powerful"},{"time":632000,"text":"for things that have"},{"time":634000,"text":"high-idling capacity."},{"time":636000,"text":"And that can be anything from baby goods"},{"time":638000,"text":"to fashions to --"},{"time":640000,"text":"how many of you have a power drill,"},{"time":642000,"text":"own a power drill? Right."},{"time":644000,"text":"That power drill will be used around 12 to 13 minutes"},{"time":647000,"text":"in its entire lifetime."},{"time":649000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":651000,"text":"It's kind of ridiculous, right?"},{"time":653000,"text":"Because what you need is the hole, not the drill."},{"time":655000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":657000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":659000,"text":"So why don't you rent the drill,"},{"time":661000,"text":"or, even better, rent out your own drill to other people"},{"time":663000,"text":"and make some money from it?"},{"time":665000,"text":"These three systems are coming together,"},{"time":668000,"text":"allowing people to share resources"},{"time":670000,"text":"without sacrificing their lifestyles,"},{"time":672000,"text":"or their cherished personal freedoms."},{"time":674000,"text":"I'm not asking people"},{"time":676000,"text":"to share nicely in the sandpit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680000,"text":"So I want to just give you an example"},{"time":682000,"text":"of how powerful collaborative consumption can be"},{"time":684000,"text":"to change behaviors."},{"time":686000,"text":"The average car"},{"time":688000,"text":"costs 8,000 dollars a year to run."},{"time":691000,"text":"Yet, that car sits idle"},{"time":693000,"text":"for 23 hours a day."},{"time":695000,"text":"So when you consider these two facts,"},{"time":697000,"text":"it starts to make a little less sense"},{"time":699000,"text":"that we have to own one outright."},{"time":702000,"text":"So this is where car-sharing companies"},{"time":704000,"text":"such as Zipcar and GoGet come in."},{"time":706000,"text":"In 2009,"},{"time":708000,"text":"Zipcar took 250 participants"},{"time":710000,"text":"from across 13 cities --"},{"time":713000,"text":"and they're all self-confessed car addicts"},{"time":715000,"text":"and car-sharing rookies --"},{"time":717000,"text":"and got them to surrender their keys for a month."},{"time":720000,"text":"Instead, these people had to walk,"},{"time":722000,"text":"bike, take the train,"},{"time":724000,"text":"or other forms of public transport."},{"time":726000,"text":"They could only use their Zipcar membership"},{"time":728000,"text":"when absolutely necessary."},{"time":730000,"text":"The results of this challenge after just one month"},{"time":733000,"text":"was staggering."},{"time":735000,"text":"It's amazing that 413 lbs were lost"},{"time":737000,"text":"just from the extra exercise."},{"time":740000,"text":"But my favorite statistic"},{"time":742000,"text":"is that 100"},{"time":744000,"text":"out of the 250 participants"},{"time":747000,"text":"did not want their keys back."},{"time":750000,"text":"In other words, the car addicts"},{"time":752000,"text":"had lost their urge to own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754000,"text":"Now products-service systems have been around for years."},{"time":757000,"text":"Just think of libraries and laundrettes."},{"time":759000,"text":"But I think they're entering a new age,"},{"time":761000,"text":"because technology makes sharing"},{"time":763000,"text":"frictionless and fun."},{"time":765000,"text":"There's a great quote that was written in the New York Times"},{"time":768000,"text":"that said, \"Sharing is to ownership"},{"time":770000,"text":"what the iPod is to the 8-track,"},{"time":773000,"text":"what solar power is to the coal mine.\""},{"time":776000,"text":"I believe also, our generation,"},{"time":779000,"text":"our relationship to satisfying what we want"},{"time":782000,"text":"is far less tangible"},{"time":784000,"text":"than any other previous generation."},{"time":786000,"text":"I don't want the DVD; I want the movie it carries."},{"time":789000,"text":"I don't want a clunky answering machine;"},{"time":791000,"text":"I want the message it saves."},{"time":793000,"text":"I don't want a CD; I want the music it plays."},{"time":796000,"text":"In other words, I don't want stuff;"},{"time":799000,"text":"I want the needs or experiences it fulfills."},{"time":802000,"text":"This is fueling a massive shift"},{"time":805000,"text":"from where usage trumps possessions --"},{"time":807000,"text":"or as Kevin Kelly, the editor of Wired magazine, puts it,"},{"time":810000,"text":"\"where access is better than ownership.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":813000,"text":"Now as our possessions"},{"time":815000,"text":"dematerialize into the cloud,"},{"time":817000,"text":"a blurry line is appearing"},{"time":819000,"text":"between what's mine, what's yours,"},{"time":821000,"text":"and what's ours."},{"time":823000,"text":"I want to give you one example"},{"time":825000,"text":"that shows how fast this evolution is happening."},{"time":828000,"text":"This represents an eight-year time span."},{"time":831000,"text":"We've gone from traditional car-ownership"},{"time":834000,"text":"to car-sharing companies, such as Zipcar and GoGet,"},{"time":837000,"text":"to ride-sharing platforms that match rides"},{"time":840000,"text":"to the newest entry, which is peer-to-peer car rental,"},{"time":843000,"text":"where you can actually make money"},{"time":846000,"text":"out of renting that car that sits idle for 23 hours a day"},{"time":849000,"text":"to your neighbor."},{"time":851000,"text":"Now all of these systems"},{"time":853000,"text":"require a degree of trust,"},{"time":855000,"text":"and the cornerstone to this working"},{"time":857000,"text":"is reputation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859000,"text":"Now in the old consumer system,"},{"time":861000,"text":"our reputation didn't matter so much,"},{"time":863000,"text":"because our credit history was far more important"},{"time":865000,"text":"that any kind of peer-to-peer review."},{"time":868000,"text":"But now with the Web, we leave a trail."},{"time":871000,"text":"With every spammer we flag,"},{"time":874000,"text":"with every idea we post, comment we share,"},{"time":877000,"text":"we're actually signaling how well we collaborate,"},{"time":879000,"text":"and whether we can or can't be trusted."},{"time":882000,"text":"Let's go back to my first example,"},{"time":884000,"text":"Swaptree."},{"time":886000,"text":"I can see that Rondoron"},{"time":888000,"text":"has completed 553 trades"},{"time":891000,"text":"with a 100 percent success rate."},{"time":894000,"text":"In other words, I can trust him or her."},{"time":898000,"text":"Now mark my words,"},{"time":900000,"text":"it's only a matter of time"},{"time":902000,"text":"before we're going to be able to perform a Google-like search"},{"time":905000,"text":"and see a cumulative picture"},{"time":907000,"text":"of our reputation capital."},{"time":909000,"text":"And this reputation capital"},{"time":911000,"text":"will determine our access to collaborative consumption."},{"time":914000,"text":"It's a new social currency, so to speak,"},{"time":916000,"text":"that could become as powerful as our credit rating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920000,"text":"Now as a closing thought,"},{"time":922000,"text":"I believe we're actually in a period"},{"time":925000,"text":"where we're waking up"},{"time":927000,"text":"from this humongous hangover"},{"time":929000,"text":"of emptiness and waste,"},{"time":931000,"text":"and we're taking a leap"},{"time":933000,"text":"to create a more sustainable system"},{"time":935000,"text":"built to serve our innate needs"},{"time":937000,"text":"for community and individual identity."},{"time":940000,"text":"I believe it will be referred to"},{"time":942000,"text":"as a revolution, so to speak --"},{"time":944000,"text":"when society, faced with great challenges,"},{"time":947000,"text":"made a seismic shift"},{"time":949000,"text":"from individual getting and spending"},{"time":951000,"text":"towards a rediscovery of collective good."},{"time":954000,"text":"I'm on a mission to make sharing cool."},{"time":957000,"text":"I'm on a mission to make sharing hip."},{"time":959000,"text":"Because I really believe"},{"time":961000,"text":"it can disrupt outdated modes of business,"},{"time":963000,"text":"help us leapfrog"},{"time":965000,"text":"over wasteful forms of hyper-consumption"},{"time":967000,"text":"and teach us when enough really is enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}